<title>REPUBLIC OF IRELAND: Lamont half-yr pre-tax profit 2.1 mln stg.</title>
<headline>Lamont half-yr pre-tax profit 2.1 mln stg.</headline>
<dateline>DUBLIN 1996-10-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Six months to June 30 1996</p>
<p>					(million stg unless stated)</p>
<p> Shr (pence)		4.68		   vs 17.96</p>
<p> Dividend (pence)	 3.65		   vs 3.65</p>
<p> Pretax profit	    2.1		    vs 7.8</p>
<p> Turnover		   58.9		   vs 65.56</p>
<p>NOTE - Northern-Ireland-based textiles group Lamont Holdings Plc said it did not expect trading conditions to materially improve in the short term.</p>
<p>It said it may have to shut down its Shaw Carpets division if losses there continued.</p>
<p>This would result in estimated closure costs of eight million stg excluding future trading losses, a cash inflow of around 4.5 million stg including the proceeds from any property disposal, and the writing-off of goodwill of 3.5 million stg, Lamont said.  </p>
<p> Operating profit	 3.00		   vs 4.22</p>
<p> Interest payable	 0.88		   vs 1.00</p>
<p> Tax charge		 0.65		   vs 2.34</p>
<p> Attributable	     1.47		   vs 5.46</p>
<p> Registration date	November 12</p>
<p> Pay date		   December 2</p>
<p>-- Dublin newsroom 353 1 660 3377</p>
